-- Taiwan finance minister asks Mega, First to study merger plans
-- By Jeanny Kao
-- Tue Mar 04, 2014 08:44PM EST
-- None



TAIPEI, March 5 (Reuters) - Taiwan's finance ministry said on Wednesday it has asked Mega Financial Holdings <2886.TW> and First Financial Holdings <2892.TW> to evaluate the possibility of merging with other state-run rivals.

Finance Minister Chang Sheng-ford told lawmakers he expects an initial outcome in the next two to four months.